==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Isoprene
<hw>I"so*prene</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Etymol.
uncertain.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>An oily, volatile unsaturated
hydrocarbon (<chform>C5H8</chform>), obtained by the distillation of
caoutchouc or gutta-percha, and used to make synthetic rubber by
polymerization. In organic chemistry, it is viewed conceptually as the
building block of the terpene series of hydrocarbons.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Isopycnic</ent>⟦br⟧
